<section class="orm-faq-section">
    <div class="container">
        <div style="text-align:center;margin-bottom:48px;">
            <span class="orm-tag">FAQ</span>
            <h2 style="font-size:clamp(22px,2.8vw,36px);font-weight:900;color:#1c1917;margin:14px 0 12px;">Frequently Asked Questions About ORM</h2>
            <p style="font-size:16px;color:var(--orm-text);max-width:620px;margin:0 auto;">Everything you need to know about our Online Reputation Management service — answered clearly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="row justify-content-center">
            <div class="col-lg-9">
                <div class="accordion" id="ormFaqAccordion">
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq1"><button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq1" aria-expanded="true">What is Online Reputation Management (ORM)?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq1" class="accordion-collapse collapse show" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">Online Reputation Management (ORM) is the strategic practice of monitoring, influencing and improving how your business is perceived online — across Google search results, review platforms, social media, AI tools, news sites, Reddit and industry directories. ORM covers proactive reputation building (generating positive reviews, authoritative content, strong Google SERP presence) and reactive reputation management (responding to negative reviews, suppressing harmful content, managing crisis situations). In 2026, ORM has expanded to include AI reputation management — managing how ChatGPT, Gemini and Perplexity represent your brand to the 45% of consumers now using AI tools for business research.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq2"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq2">How much does a bad online reputation cost a business?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">93% of consumers rely on online reviews before buying — meaning almost every potential customer sees your reviews. 86% are deterred by 1-2 star reviews, creating an immediate and ongoing revenue drain. Each additional star in a Yelp rating increases revenue by up to 9%. Healthcare providers lose an average of $47,000 per negative review. Legal services lose $32,000 per review. Over 90% of individuals believe ORM directly influences at least 25% of a company's total market value — representing $11.9 trillion of S&P 500 value tied to reputation.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq3"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq3">How long does it take to repair a damaged reputation?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq3" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">Review rating improvements typically become visible within 60 to 90 days of a systematic review generation programme. SERP reputation management — suppressing negative search results and building a positive Page 1 presence — typically takes 3 to 6 months for meaningful movement, with sustained improvement at 6 to 12 months. Crisis recovery requires both immediate damage control (15-30 minutes for initial response) and a sustained 6-12 month positive content rebuilding programme. Proactive ORM — starting before any crisis — is always faster and cheaper than reactive repair.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq4"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq4">What is AI Reputation Management and why does it matter in 2026?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq4" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">AI Reputation Management monitors and influences how ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI Overviews represent your brand. In 2026, 45% of consumers use AI tools for business recommendations — up from just 6% in 2025. Critically, 85% of AI brand mentions come from third-party sources, not your own website. This means AI systems build their opinion of your brand primarily from reviews, news, social media and third-party content. If those sources are negative or absent, AI will represent you poorly to nearly half of all potential buyers.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq5"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq5">What is the difference between ORM and SEO?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq5" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">SEO improves the ranking of your own web pages for relevant keywords. ORM controls what appears on Page 1 when someone searches for your brand name — ensuring it is positive, accurate and brand-controlled. ORM uses many SEO techniques (content creation, link building, SERP strategy) but applies them specifically to brand name searches rather than keyword searches. ORM also extends beyond search engines to review platforms, social media, AI tools, news sites and industry directories — everywhere your brand reputation lives online.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq6"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq6">Can negative Google reviews be removed?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq6" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">Google removes reviews that violate its policies — fake reviews, spam, inappropriate content or reviews from people who never interacted with your business. Reviews representing genuine customer experiences cannot be removed for being unflattering. Effective strategies include: responding promptly and professionally (45% of consumers more likely to visit businesses that respond to negative reviews), flagging genuine policy violations for removal, and generating strong positive review volume to dilute isolated negatives. Authentic review generation is the only sustainable long-term strategy.</div></div></div>
                    <div class="accordion-item"><h2 class="accordion-header" id="ormFaq7"><button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#ormfaq7">How do you monitor online reputation?</button></h2><div id="ormfaq7" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#ormFaqAccordion"><div class="accordion-body">We monitor every channel where your brand reputation lives: Google Business Profile and all major review platforms (Trustpilot, G2, Glassdoor, Yelp, industry-specific), Google SERP Page 1 for brand name searches, social media mentions and sentiment across all major platforms, news and press coverage, AI platform mentions (ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity), Reddit and community forums. We provide real-time alerts for high-priority mentions and a comprehensive monthly reputation health report across all monitored channels.</div></div></div>
